  "market_context": "An ongoing uptrend with sequential higher highs and higher lows; the analyst focuses on a specific segment where price forms a higher low but RSI forms a lower low, indicating hidden bullish divergence.",
  "key_observation": "Price printed a higher low while the RSI indicator simultaneously printed a lower low—this mismatch signals a hidden bullish divergence and uptrend continuation.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst identified swing lows on the price chart (higher high → higher low → higher high → higher low sequence).",
    "Step 2: The analyst compared those price lows with corresponding RSI values, noting that from one low to the next, price made a higher low but RSI made a lower low.",
    "Step 3: The analyst confirmed this as a hidden bullish divergence, emphasizing it is a continuation signal (not reversal) in an existing uptrend.",
    "Step 4: The analyst contrasted this with standard bullish divergence (reversal) to clarify the distinction."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Hidden bullish divergence occurs when price makes higher lows but the oscillator (RSI) makes lower lows during an uptrend—it confirms trend strength and suggests continuation, not reversal.",
